Nash & Brother succeeds Duane H. Nash in New York, New York by 1872. Acme Harrow Company (Millington, New Jersey) is founded by Frederick Nishwitz (1829-1900) in 1879. Duane H. Nash (Firm) succeeds Acme Harrow Company in 1882? when Duane H. Nash (1843-1905) takes over management of the company. By 1884 Nash & Brother moves from New York, New York to Millington, New Jersey. Duane H. Nash, Inc. is incorporated in 1905 upon death of Duane H. Nash (1843-1905). Nash Acme Harrow Company (Philadelphia, Pennsylvania) is incorporated in 1924 with Duane H. Nash, Jr., as sales manager.

title: Nash & Brother

definition: Preferred form of name for use in Iowa State University Library metadata.
usage: Use this name to describe resources by or about the entity that existed in New York, New York in the 1870s and Millington, New Jersey in the 1880s. Review and assign related terms as appropriate, based on the following information (which, it should be noted, involves guesswork with some dates and corporate relationships unclear). Nash & Brother succeeds Duane H. Nash in New York, New York by 1872. Acme Harrow Company (Millington, New Jersey) is founded by Frederick Nishwitz (1829-1900) in 1879. Duane H. Nash (Firm) succeeds Acme Harrow Company in 1882? when Duane H. Nash (1843-1905) takes over management of the company. By 1884 Nash & Brother moves from New York, New York to Millington, New Jersey. Duane H. Nash, Inc. is incorporated in 1905 upon death of Duane H. Nash (1843-1905). Nash Acme Harrow Company (Philadelphia, Pennsylvania) is incorporated in 1924 with Duane H. Nash, Jr., as sales manager.
